SUBSECTION.TEXT:
A queue is a sequence in which items are inserted at one end (called the queuerear of rear of the queue) and deleted from the other end (the queuefront of front).
Figure Figure
shows an initially empty queue in which the items a and b are inserted. Then a is removed, c and d are inserted, and b is removed. Because items are always removed in the order in which they are inserted, a queue is sometimes called a FIFO buffer FIFO (first in, first out) buffer.
